==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Porridge
<hw>Por"ridge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably corrupted
fr. <ets>pottage</ets>; perh. influenced by OE. <ets>porree</ets> a kind
of pottage, OF. <ets>porr⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, fr. L. <ets>porrum</ets>,
<ets>porrus</ets>, leek. See <er>Pottage</er>, and cf.
<er>Porringer</er>.]</ety> <def>A food made by boiling some leguminous
or farinaceous substance, or the meal of it, in water or in milk, making
of broth or thin pudding; <as>as, barley <ex>porridge</ex>, milk
<ex>porridge</ex>, bean <ex>porridge</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porringer</ent>⟦br⟧
